# Operator reconcile loop

Skill: `@kubernetes-operator` · References: [reconcile_loop.md](../skills/kubernetes-operator/references/reconcile_loop.md)

Project ADRs: [ADR-003](../../docs/02-technical-design/decision-records/architecture/003-neo4j-reconcile-pipeline.md), [ADR-004](../../docs/02-technical-design/decision-records/architecture/004-status-and-conditions.md), [ADR-008](../../docs/02-technical-design/decision-records/architecture/008-finalizers-and-deletion.md)

## Shape

Reconcile is **declarative**: make `actual == desired` idempotently — not "if creating / if updating / if deleting".

```
fetch CR → deletion/finalizer → set Reconciling → work (domain steps) → status().Update → requeue or done
```

## Must

- Return `(ctrl.Result, error)`; requeue transient errors (`Requeue` or `RequeueAfter`)
- Update **status subresource only** via `r.Status().Update` — never write user-owned spec fields
- Use finalizers for external cleanup; pair `AddFinalizer` with `RemoveFinalizer`
- Set `OwnerReferences` on owned child objects
- Keep controller `Reconcile()` thin (~150 lines); delegate to `internal/domain/*` per ADR-002
- Enable leader election when replicas > 1

## Must not

- `time.Sleep` in reconcile — use `RequeueAfter`
- Long blocking HTTP/RPC without `context` cancellation
- `r.Client.Update` on the CR to patch status fields
- Observe-then-act loops inside one reconcile without caching reads

## Before merge

```bash
python3 .cursor/skills/kubernetes-operator/scripts/reconcile_lint.py --controller src/internal/controller/
